    "name": "Night Of The Abattoir Man",
    "steam_appid": 3020780,
    "required_age": 0,
    "is_free": true,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/225ace5d842ce6f4532a67011fc5dac0.avif?t=1771427845\" width=439 height=194 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>STORY:</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >In New York, there lives a legend of a monster known as the <strong>Abattoir Man</strong>, a 10 foot tall bloodthirsty maniac. A beast so tall he blocks the moon, so heavy the ground shakes beneath him, so strong he bends steel like paper and with eyes so empty and cold that one single glare is enough to freeze your whole body.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >To many, this simply a legend. But to young Michael D'Amato, the legend will soon become a life changing night of terror as he is forced to escape the monster himself.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Will Michael be just another victim to the merciless cleaver of the mad butcher or will he get away, and if he does survive what will be left to tell the tale?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game is incredibly tense, harrowing and terrifying while not being devoid of humor. As Sam Raimi once said, horror and comedy go hand to hand. However, this game tackles incredibly disturbing and gruesome topics, topics that it of course takes completely seriously. And of course, there's lot's of <strong>GORE</strong>, lot's and lot's of gore.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Night of the Abattoir Man has everything to be among the classics of the rpg maker horror genre like Mad Father, The Witch's House and Ao Oni. So go ahead, play it and see for yourself.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Can you survive the <strong>Night of the Abattoir Man</strong>?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/5ce2036ac245fa1b0568ab3bb7064684.avif?t=1771427845\" width=640 height=480 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Gameplay:</strong> </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/3409fd4713d204ca921e6e0d63d2ef64.gif?t=1771427845\"><img src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/3409fd4713d204ca921e6e0d63d2ef64.poster.avif?t=1771427845\" class=\"bb_img\" /></picture></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >In the game your play as Michael D'Amato, a young 23 year old college graduate from Naples Italy. As Michael, you're chased into the old ruins of the Sassafraz Factory. Your objective then is simple, find a way out of the factory and escape the Abattoir Man. You will have to explore the maps, solve puzzles and find keys all while being stalked the the towering beast himself. And all you can do to defend yourself is run, hide and set up traps to delay the unstopable butcher. Occasionally you're met with boss encounters after each level to shake up gameplay.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You will also be able to find secrets, all filled with references to other games and movies. Can you find all of them?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >After you beat the neutral ending, you unlock the Abattoir Man himself as a playable character. you're objective here is even simpler, kill Michael. But nothing is stopping you from exploring the map. and who knows, you might just find something... unexpected...</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/b94c1f1677c6368b329401d465122e92.poster.avif?t=1771427845\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/b94c1f1677c6368b329401d465122e92.webm?t=1771427845\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/b94c1f1677c6368b329401d465122e92.mp4?t=1771427845\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Features:</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >- The game allows you to play as two characters: Michael D'Amato, the victim, or Trevor Hartman, the Abattoir Man.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/d7c189db769d9f417ba91231fd4da4f3.poster.avif?t=1771427845\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/d7c189db769d9f417ba91231fd4da4f3.webm?t=1771427845\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/d7c189db769d9f417ba91231fd4da4f3.mp4?t=1771427845\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >- The graphics are inspired by anime and the look of old 80s MS-DOS and Commodore 64 games, giving it a nice retro style charm.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/2c7ce8d6bcba21a9c910e6e6cac55c6b.avif?t=1771427845\" width=640 height=480 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >- The game features multiple endings, encouraging replayability.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3020780/extras/21a9deea5004ff5254632dbf3d4e6c48.avif?t=1771427845\" width=640 height=480 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
